documentation.author: CERNER INNOVATION
documentation.purpose:
1. To increase the percentage of hospitalized adult patients (18 years and older) : --- who are appropriately assessed for venous thromboembolism (VTE) risk. --- who are at risk of VTE who have received education for VTE that includes VTE risk signs and symptoms and treatment/prophylaxis methods available. --- who begin early and frequent ambulation to reduce VTE risk. --- receiving appropriate pharmacological and/or mechanical prophylaxis treatment.
2. To reduce the risk of complications from pharmacologic prophylaxis.
documentation.explanation:
First Workflow option evoke with trigger orderable: Add from PowerOrders OR Initiate from PowerPlan with "VTE Prophylaxis Guideline" orderable AND Encounter Type = Inpatient AND Age >= 18
Second Workflow option of MPage
The advisor will be made available as an MPage in Powerchart for the physician and nurse position. Recommendations will only appear as text instead of orders. MPage functionality must be purchased and downloaded separately from this content package.
(The following is what shows in the html - next to each item is the corresponding logic template i.e. L31)
Section 1: Current State A. Most recent Risk Category (L31) Display the most recent result for clinical event D-VTE risk category for the current encounter or most recent for previous encounters up to last 30 days.
B. Relevant Lab Data (L443 - L467) Display the following lab results with date (limit to last 30 days except PF4 - limit to last 100 days): 1. PT 2. PTT 3. INR 4. Platelets 5. PF4 Display "No relevant lab data found" if nothing found.
C. Relevant active orders and/or home medications 1. Pharmacologic Orders a. Active Order for Drug Classes anticoagulants, thrombolytics, and recombinant human erythropoietins Display (drug and dose) (L35 - L37) b. Incoming Order for Drug Classes anticoagulants, thrombolytics, and recombinant human erythropoietins (L41) c. Home medications/Prescriptions (current) for drug classes anticoagulants, thrombolytics, and recombinant human erythropoietins (L42 - L44) 2. Mechanical Orders (L39 & L40) a. Below the Knee Graduated Compression Stocking b. Below the Knee Intermittent Pneumatic Compression Device c. Foot Pump Display "No relevant data found" if nothing found.
Section 2: Patient Types Medical Minor Surgery (procedure less than 30 minutes) (L250 - 252) Ortho Surgery - Elective hip replacement (L253 - 255) Ortho Surgery - Elective knee replacement (L256 - 258) Ortho Surgery - Knee arthroscopy (L259 - 261) Ortho Surgery - Hip fracture surgery (L262 - 264) Ortho Surgery - Elective spine surgery (L265 - 267) Ortho, other (L268 - 270) Ortho Surgery - Lower extremity injuries distal to the knee Neurosurgery (L271 - 273) Vascular Surgery (L274 - 276) Gynecological Surgery - Minor (procedure less than 30 minutes) (L277 - 279) Gynecological Surgery -Entirely Laparoscopic (L280 - 282) Gynecological Surgery -Major (procedure greater than 30 minutes) (L283 - 285) Urologic Surgery - Transurethral or other low risk procedures (L286 - 288) Urologic Surgery - Major, open (L289 - 291) Entirely Laparoscopic Procedure (L292 - 294) Bariatric Surgery (L295 - 297) Thoracic Surgery (L298 - 300) CABG/Valve Surgery (L301 - 303) General Surgery (L307 - 309) Trauma Spinal Cord Injury Burn Pregnancy/Post-Partum (female only) (L304 - 306)
Section 3: Risk Factors
A. Risk Factors For all patient types EXCEPT Pregnant/Post Partum
-Condition-Related Risks Cancer Malignant (L51 - L59) Previous DVT and/or PE (L60 - L68) Cardiac dysfunction (L69 - L77) Severe Respiratory dysfunction (L78 - L86) Acute Ischemic Stroke (L87 - L95) Inflammatory disease (L96 - L104) Infection, Severe/Systemic (L105 - L109) Nephrotic syndrome (110- L114) Trauma (L115 - L119) Pregnancy or postpartum (female only) (L120 - L128) Varicose Veins (L129 - L137) Hypercoagulable states (L138 - L142)
-Patient-Related Risks Obesity (L143 - L146) ICU Admission (L147 - L149) Central Venous Catheter (L150 - L155) Mechanical Ventilation (L156 - L161) Immobility (L162 - L171) Estrogen use (female only) (L172 - L175) Erythropoiesis-stimulating agents (L176 - L179)
B. Risk Factors for Patient Type Pregnant/Post Partum -Condition-Related Risks Previous DVT and/or PE (L60 - L68) Infection, Severe/Systemic (L105 - L109) Varicose Veins (L129 - L137) Preeclampsia (L180 - L184) Major current illness (e.g. congestive heart failure, inflammatory bowel disease, nephritic syndrome) Postcesarean hysterectomy Paralysis of lower limbs Thrombophilia (L185 - 189) Presence of antiphospholipid antibodies
-Patient Related Age greater or equal to 35 Obesity (L143 - L146) Multiparity (greater or equal to 4) (L190 - 193) Long Labor (greater or equal to 18 hours) (L194 - L197) Immobility of more than 4 days prior to surgery
Other None
Section 4: Pharmacologic Contraindications -Absolute Coagulopathy (non-therapeutic) (L198 - L202) Active bleeding History of heparin induced thrombocytopenia (HIT) (L203 - 207) Thrombolytics given within the past 24 hours (L208 - 214) Severe trauma Spinal or epidural catheter within next 24 hours. -Absolute/Relative: Thombocytopenia (L215 - L218) Hypertension (L219 - L226) Infective endocarditis (L227 - 231) Active hepatitis or hepatic insuffic iency (L232 - 236 Other, absolute Other, relative
Section 5: Renal Function and Rapid Onset HIT
-Is Creatinine Clearance (Cockcroft-Gault) less than or equal to 30 mL/min? (L246 - L249) -Has the patient received unfractionated heparin within the last 100 days? (L237 - L 245)
Section 5 or 6. Mechanical Contraindications Bilateral lower extremity amputation Bilateral lower extremity trauma Other None
documentation.impact:
***IMPORTANT INFORMATION - PLEASE READ***
For further set up instructions including test scripts, please refer to the Supplemental Documentation included within the Content Package.
If the level of code is less than 2007.18, to handle the size of this rule, the thread_stacksz property will need to be modified to equal 400,000 on server 175, Discern Expert CPM.EKS.
EVOKE SECTION: ADDTOSCRATCHPAD E1 - The orderable VTE Prophylaxis Guidelines is used to trigger the Discern Advisor. This orderable can be chosen from the order catalog or used within a PowerPlan. This orderable will need to be built in the domain and mapped or reinstantiated in the rule.
SYNCHEVENT E1 - This evoke enables this VTE Advisor to be launch from an MPage, as an MPage on it's own PowerChart tab or from a link within another MPage. The license for MPages must be purchased and components downloaded for this functionality.
If accessing the Discern Advisor from a tab in PowerChart, the text following the colons below needs to be included in the parameters named when adding the Discern Report tab for a specified position at the chart level in PrefMaint.exe.
For Report Name: eks_call_synch_event For Report Parameters: "MINE","$pat_personid$","$vis_encntrid$","0.0","vte_advisor_link","$usr_personid$"
If accessing the Discern Advisor from a hyperlink embedded in another MPage, use the same items within the appropriate CCLLINK function, however in the parameters that are closed in with $, you will need to instead put a variable representing the person id, encounter id, and user id.
LOGIC SECTION: ALL EKS_BUILD_MESSAGE templates: No modification needed UNLESS the numbers of the substitution values need to be changed due to addition or deletion of other templates. These templates are used to collect data and send it to the .html file to fill in variables. Do NOT modify the names in the MSGNAME parameters.
L3 - The orderable VTE Prophylaxis Guidelines is used to trigger the Discern Advisor from ADDTOSCRATCHPAD. This orderable can be chosen from the order catalog or used within a PowerPlan. This orderable will need to be built in the domain and mapped or reinstantiated in the rule.
L4 and L11 are placeholders, these can be changed to fit a site specific need, i.e. position or location information. If that is not needed, they must remain in the rule and do NOT delete them. If they are deleted, all substitution values will need to be modified. They will not take up extra processing time for the rule.
L5 - DETAIL_VALUE parameter needs to be reinstantiated with client specific database build. Recommendations include INPATIENT and EMERGENCY encounter types from code set 71.
L6, 7, 10, 12 - No modification needed. This is a script to identify the recipient of the Discern Advisor. This is used within the clinical_event that is posted to the patient's recored to save the recommendation by the rule ADVSR_VTE_POST_3.
L36, 39, 46, L49 - Script used to find all of the details for the lab results or orders identified and found in the proceeding corresponding templates.
L147 patient location of ICU needs to be reinstantiated with client specific database build with all of the ICU locations that patients could be registered to. If patient is located in the ICU this is considered a "risk". Note: this template is not making this rule only fire on ICU patients.
L250 - 307 templates looking for existing orders to prepopulate the patient type.
L310 - 441 These templates deal with building the order lists that will show within the Advisor. The orders are chosen in the templates name EKS_ADVISOR_ORDERABLES_L and then the order details are associated to the orders using templates named EKS_ADVISOR_ORDERDETAILS_L. There are mutliples lists built to show up in the appropriate recommendation. The orderables and specific order details need to be reinstantiated with client specific order catalog items and order details to duplicate what is listed to match the specific recommendations within the Advisor. Do NOT modify the name of the orderlist. If allergies are found, the orderlists will be blank and a flag is set in a build message template. **The Advisor is coded to allow for all fondaparinux order lists to be removed if fondaparinux is not in the formulary.
In the EKS_ADVISOR_ORDERABLES_L templates, the ORDERS parameter needs to be reinstantiated with client specific database build. The orderables in these parameters match specific recommendations with the .html file. Orderables chosen for these templates should closely/exactly match the existing order names. Do NOT modify the name of the orderlist.
In the EKS_ADVISOR_ORDERDETAILS_L templates, the ORDER_DETAIL and DETAIL_VALUE parameters need to be reinstantiated with client specific database build. These order details will be associated to the orderables chosen in the corresponding order lists. Do NOT modify the name of the orderlist.
L442 If the user wants to exit the Advisor without documenting a risk category & placing orders, a deferral reason must be indicated. This list is built in this template and can be modified to fit your needs. You can add to this list, remove items, and modify items. There are 3 default reasons built and located in the MSGTEXT parameter. Each reason must be separated by the "|" character as shown in this template. i.e. Already addressed|Defer to other physician|Advisor entered by mistake (wrong patient)
ACTION: Action Group 1: For ADDTOSCRATCHPAD Evoke: A1 HTML_FILE parameter holds the path to the location of the advsr_vte_10.html that corresponds to this rule. The default path included within the rules in the action section template is pointed to the cer_install directory using the cer_install: logical. HTML files should be saved in a read-only directory that does not get deleted or overwritten. The OPT_FREETEXT_PARAM must be set to a value of either 1 or 0. A value of 1 will cancel the incoming order that triggers the Advisor. A value of 0 will allow the order to be added to the orders tab and ready for signing. Depending upon the evoke of a single orderable or an orderable within an orderset, it may be necessary to build action groups to accommodate which value is needed to be used. The default is set to 1 due to the fact the incoming order is simply used to trigger the Advisor and may not need to be signed and kept on the medical record.
Action Group 1: For SYNCHEVENT Evoke: A1 HTML_FILE parameter holds the path to the location of the advsr_vte_10.html that corresponds to this rule. The default path included within the rules in the action section template is pointed to the cer_install directory using the cer_install: logical. HTML files should be saved in a read-only directory that does not get deleted or overwritten.
For further set up instructions including test scripts, please refer to the Supplemental Documentation included within the Content Package.
